  "original_text": "Sutra Sthana, Adhyaya 8 — Indriyopakramaniya

atha khalv indriyopakramanīyam adhyāyam vyākhyāsyāmaḥ || 
iti ha smāha bhagavān ātreyaḥ ||

[Key verses on sense-organ care:]

cakṣuṣyāṇi — añjana (sauvirāñjana, rasāñjana, srotoñjana), karañja taila, triphalā, yaṣṭīmadhu, madhuka, saindhava, candana, śatāvarī, śāliparṇī, haridrā, dārvī;

śrotrendriya — tilataila, bilva, nirgundi, śatāvarī, aśvagandhā, balā;

nāsā — aṇu taila (pratimarśa nasya), brahmi ghṛta, vacā, śigru, pippalī, saindhava lavana;

jihvā / rasanendriya — tāmbūla sevana, lavaṇa, āmalakī, pippalī, marica;

tvak / sparśanendriya — abhyañga with tila taila, mustā, elā, candana, aguru, karpūra;

buddhi-indriya-prasādanam — brahmi, śaṅkhapuṣpī, vacā, kuṣmāṇḍa, jīvantī, aśvagandhā, ghṛta (medicated);",
  "translation": "Now we shall explain the chapter on the care and upkeep of the sense organs [Indriyopakramaniya], as taught by the venerable Atreya.

The sense organs [indriya] — sight [cakṣus], hearing [śrotra], smell [ghrāṇa], taste [rasana], and touch [tvak] — along with the mind [manas] as the sixth sense, require systematic care through appropriate dietary, behavioral, and therapeutic regimens. The following substances and practices are described:

**I. Care of the Eyes (Cakṣurindriya)**
Substances beneficial to the eyes [cakṣuṣya] include:
- Collyrium preparations [añjana]: sauvirāñjana (antimony / stibnite), rasāñjana (extract of Berberis aristata, Indian barberry), and srotoñjana (a pure mineral collyrium). These are applied to the eyes for cleansing, strengthening vision, and treating inflammatory conditions.
- Karañja oil [karañja taila] (Pongamia pinnata): used in ocular washes.
